    "created_at": "2016-10-08T13:00:27Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-10-08T13:01:13Z",
    "body": "This doesn't seem to happen if you leave DISPLAY set.\n\n```\n    env: { 'DISPLAY': process.env.DISPLAY },\n```\n\nThat seems to be well documented in [docs/tutorial/testing-on-headless-ci.md](https://github.com/electron/electron/blob/master/docs/tutorial/testing-on-headless-ci.md).\n\n> Being based on Chromium, Electron requires a display driver to function. If Chromium can't find a display driver, Electron will simply fail to launch\n"
